                  <summary>1 copy of Bāb-i haftum dar imāmat by ʿAbd al-ʿAzīz Dihlavī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008111617 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064479" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_812x-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658519.0x000001 viaf_53999017">ʿAbd al-ʿAzīz Dihlavī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658519.0x000001 viaf_53999017">عبد العزيز دهلوى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21787">Bāb-i haftum dar imāmat</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_21787">باب هفتم در امامت</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Excerpt from a theological treatise (specifically, chapter seven,) dealing with the subject of imamate ascribed to the muḥaddis̲ of Shahjahanabad Delhi, 
                <persName key="viaf_53999017" role="aut">Shāh ʿAbd al-ʿAzīz ibn Aḥmad Valī Allāh al-ʿUmarī al-Dihlavī</persName>(d. 1239/1824).
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                        <p>Coarse nastaʿlīq declining into shikastah āmīz.</p>
                        <p>Stamped foliation.</p>
                        <p>Plain paper dust wrapper; watermarked (seated Britannia or Minerva in crowned oval frame, initialled RBLd; 
                <orgName>Rock Brothers Limited</orgName>, Superfine; not dated); labels, torn, creased and stained.
                        </p>
                        <p>Folios unbound; creased, torn, stained, wormholes.</p>
                        <p>Condition fragile.</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
